
The configure scripts are only useful on UNIX-type systems. To
use, simply type the following at the command prompt:

prompt> ./configure
prompt> make


The configuration files that can be changed:

	openexif/Makefile.am
	openexif/configure.in
	openexif/acconfig.h
	openexif/config.h.in
	openexif/bootstrap
	
	openexif/src/Makefile.am

	Custom m4 macros:
	openexif/config-scripts/ac_compile_ansi.m4 	- check/set ansi mode
	openexif/config-scripts/ac_compile_warning.m4	- turn on full warning mode
	openexif/config-scripts/ac_sys_posix.m4		- set POSIX mode


Automatically generated configuration files 
that are not to be changed:

	openexif/configure			- generated by autoconf from configure.in
	openexif/libtool			- generated by autoconf

	openexif/config-scripts/depcomp		- used by automake / Makefile
	openexif/config-scripts/install-sh	- used by automake / Makefile
	openexif/config-scripts/config.guess	- used by autoconf
	openexif/config-scripts/config.sub	- used by autoconf
	openexif/config-scripts/ltconfig	- used by libtool
	openexif/config-scripts/ltmain.sh	- used by libtool
	openexif/config-scripts/missing		- used by automake / autoconf
	openexif/config-scripts/mkinstalldirs	- used by automake / Makefile

	openexif/Makefile.in			- generated by automake
	openexif/src/Makefile.in		- generated by automake

	openexif/Makefile			- generated by configure
	openexif/src/Makefile			- generated by configure

Once a configuration file is changed, run the following
commands from within the EkTiff root directory:

	-> ./bootstrap
	-> ./configure

this will update the configuration and Makefiles.

NOTE: must use automake v1.4a or greater
